This paper deals with modeling and analyzing the capacity of a fiber optic channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the nonlinearity of the channel, which falls under optics (cs.OH) and physics (cs.PH). Finally, the paper proposes an achievable bound on channel capacity, which involves mathematical optimization and signal processing (cs.SI).
